text: Highway 5 (, Kvish 5, or Trans-Samaria Highway , Kvish Hotze Shomron) is a highway between Israel and the West Bank. It runs east to west. The road starts in Glilot Ma'arav Interchange in Tel Aviv and ends in Ariel Junction near the settlement of Ariel. == Other websites == Category:Roads in Israel Category:West Bank
